08,01 -15-14-------------------------------------------------------------------------15-08-



08,01    F15irst off, MRi is a general net with no theme whatsoever, and we
15,01    gladly give smaller ansi, programming, cracking, and warez groups
15,01    the chance to use MRi as the communications hub of their group.
15,01    Because of the loose structure, we aren't looking for any particular
15,01    type of board: may it be art, warez, music, programming, or any
15,01    other type of board, as long as you have good posters, and free
15,01    space on your HD, we welcome you.  All it takes is the completion
15,01    of the application.

15,01    08S15econd, acceptance into MRi does not mean you are a member for
15,01    eternity. If at any point the other sysops feel that your board is
15,01    no longer adequate, or has done too many stupid things, then you
15,01    will be nuked, and must re-apply later. This is only to keep the
15,01    net in a shapely order, and is NOT meant as a tool of revenge. The
15,01    only way you can be kicked off is by a unanimous agreement among
15,01    the other sysops.

15,01    08T15hird, MRi is a Fido-compatible network. This means that we
15,01    comply with all standards set forth by the developers of the Fido
15,01    standard. On a Fido-compatible network, you must make sure that
15,01    your posters are aware of the ansi standards. We do allow the use
15,01    of system specific color codes (i.e. |xx, ^x, @xx, etc.) but it
15,01    MUST be known to all that ansis posted MUST be saved in the
15,01    following format:
15,01       1) Line length of 69-71 characters
15,01       2) No 80th column characters
15,01       3) No animation
15,01    08I15f you stay within these guidelines, the pictures will be clear on
15,01    all nodes, and will avoid garbagy messages from your system. If
15,01    there is a continuous flow of ansis saved incorrectly from your
15,01    board, then it may be grounds for expulsion from the net.

15,01    08F15ourth, if your group would like a base to be sanctioned by you,
15,01    just ask. You must have at least three (3) boards from your group
15,01    already on the net, and a belief that good discussion will come
15,01    from the base. If you find this the case, then just let us know as
15,01    soon as you are accepted, and the next echolist will include your
15,01    base. We are currently sanctioned by the following groups (some
15,01    with bases, some without)

15,01         Alive - Apex - Radian - Relic - Rem - TSC - Union - UPA

15,01    08F15inally, the application process is easy.  Download the latest
15,01    nodelist from one of the above hubs or FREQ it from the WHQ
15,01    (Packaged Rebellion).  Fill out the enclosed application and
15,01    send it to one of the hubs. The sysop will then post your
15,01    application in a voting base, where you will be voted on.
15,01    If you are accepted, you will be contacted via voice
15,01    (or by other means) within a week. However, if you are rejected,
15,01    you will not be contacted at all. Take note that sometimes it
15,01    may take longer than a week, but usually not. There is no limit
